31/03/2006
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Republika Srpska (RS) Prime Minister Milorad Dodik said Thursday (30 March) that a special police department tasked with hunting down war criminals and investigating their network of supporters was being established.
Speaking to Radio Free Europe, he also said the RS government would allow investigators from the UN war crimes tribunal in The Hague permanent presence within the new department.
(RTRS - 30/03/06)
